Last year the department of transport introduced a system to help ease the driver’s license backlog which frustrated motorists. We’re joined by Maputla Makgatho from the department of licensing and consumer affairs to give us an update. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Approximately 124,000 South African's are driving without their card license. That backlog is due to a faulty printing issue. WATCH: Proposal for motorists to retake driving test every 5 years Maputla Makgatho from the department of licensing and consumer affairs explained to eNCA what the issues where. He says the massive backlog will be cleared in two months.